title: Static Analysis

android.permission.INTERNET.description: Allows an application to create network sockets.

android.permission.USE_FINGERPRINT.description: This constant was deprecated in API level 28. Applications should request USE_BIOMETRIC instead

android.permission.CAMERA.description: Allows application to take pictures and videos with the camera. This allows the application to collect images that the camera is seeing at any time.

android.permission.READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE.description: Allows an application to read from external storage.

android.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAG.description: Allows an application to write to external storage.

android.permission.VIBRATE.description: Allows the application to control the vibrator.

android.permission.RECEIVE_BOOT_COMPLETE.description: Allows an application to start itself as soon as the system has finished booting. This can make it take longer to start the phone and allow the application to slow down the overall phone by always running.

android.permission.ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE.description: Allows an application to view the status of all networks.

android.permission.ACCESS_WIFI_STATE.description: Allows an application to view the information about the status of Wi-Fi.

manifest_analysis.title:
Application Data can be Backed up
[android:allowBackup] flag is missing.
manifest_analysis.desc: The flag [android:allowBackup] should be set to false. By default it is set to true and allows anyone to backup your application data via adb. It allows users who have enabled USB debugging to copy application data off of the device.
manifest_analysis.name: Application Data can be Backed up [android:allowBackup] flag is missing.

nx.description: The shared object has NX bit set. This marks a memory page non-executable making attacker injected shellcode non-executable.

stack_canary.description: This shared object has a stack canary value added to the stack so that it will be overwritten by a stack buffer that overflows the return address. This allows detection of overflows by verifying the integrity of the canary before function return.

relocation_readonly.description: This shared object has full RELRO enabled. RELRO ensures that the GOT cannot be overwritten in vulnerable ELF binaries. In Full RELRO, the entire GOT (.got and .got.plt both) is marked as read-only.

rpath.description: The shared object does not have run-time search path or RPATH set.

runpath.description: The shared object does not have RUNPATH set.

fortify.description: The shared object does not have any fortified functions. Fortified functions provides buffer overflow checks against glibc's commons insecure functions like strcpy, gets etc. Use the compiler option -D_FORTIFY_SOURCE=2 to fortify functions.

nx.description: The shared object does not have NX bit set. NX bit offer protection against exploitation of memory corruption vulnerabilities by marking memory page as non-executable. Use option --noexecstack or -z noexecstack to mark stack as non executable.

stack_canary.description: This shared object does not have a stack canary value added to the stack. Stack canaries are used to detect and prevent exploits from overwriting return address. Use the option -fstack-protector-all to enable stack canaries.

relocation_readonly.description: This shared object does not have RELRO enabled. The entire GOT (.got and .got.plt both) are writable. Without this compiler flag, buffer overflows on a global variable can overwrite GOT entries. Use the option -z,relro,-z,now to enable full RELRO and only -z,relro to enable partial RELRO.

playstore_details.title: eXchangily DEX Bitcoin Wallet & Crypto Wallet
playstore_details.description:
Designed and built in the USA, eXchangily is the world's first open-source, multi-chain DEX. The eXchangily wallet is your gateway to the eXchangily DEX and the first step to autonomous crypto ownership. The eXchangily DEX is currently in a late stage Beta release, so keep a close eye on us as our world class team continues to eradicate the boundaries and restrictions of traditional exchanges as we bring the benefits and freedoms of decentralization to masses. Join us in the crypto revolution, install eXchangily today.

The eXchangily app is a native multi-chain wallet that provides an interface to the eXchangily DEX. With eXchangily, you own and control your private key, ensuring your crypto assets are kept in your wallet, giving you absolute control and 100% autonomous ownership. Use your wallet for native multi-chain peer-to peer transfers and rest assured that your crypto assets can never be frozen by us or any third party. Welcome to decentralization!

The eXchangily DEX is a secure, lightning fast, low cost per transaction exchange that runs on top of the public Fast Access Blockchain (FAB). FAB and eXchangily are developed by the same team, architected from the ground up to address the challenges and constraints of decentralization at an enterprise scale. We are introducing new features and trading pairs to the DEX weekly, so follow us closely.

FAB and eXchangily are open source projects, unlike other exchanges we have nothing to hide, anyone can see our code at any time. eXchangily is the first truly transparent and trustworthy decentralized exchange, no false figure reporting, no inflated volumes, no washing and no nonsense. Everything is on the block chain.

View our open source code on GitHub here

Features: eXchangily is S.A.F.E
Secure
• Your private key and transaction data is always kept on your device in your eXchangily Bitcoin Wallet and Crypto Wallet and is always encrypted so no one can see or access your crypto currency but you

Autonomous
• You are in total control of your eXchangily Bitcoin Wallet and Crypto Wallet, your tokens are in your wallet, no one can take, use or lock your tokens at any time.

Fast
• You’ve likely never heard the words fast and blockchain in the same sentence until now. Welcome to eXchangily where we utilize the FAB public blockchain to operate at the speed of business.

Easy
• It is imperative to the team that the eXchangily user interface be simple and intuitive to use in order to enhance our users experience.

To find out more about eXchangily visit our website click here
